[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Is my midea unit ine of the recalled units https://www.cpsc.gov/Recalls/2025/Midea-Recalls-About-1-7-Million-U-and-U-Window-Air-Conditioners-Due-to-Risk-of-Mold-Exposure Midea Recalls About 1.7 Million U and U+ Window Air Conditioners ... https://www.cpsc.gov/Recalls/2025/Midea-Recalls-About-1-7-Million-U-and-U-Window-Air-Conditioners-Due-to-Risk-of-Mold-Exposure 1.7 Million Midea Air Conditioners Recalled Due to Mold Risk https://www.consumerreports.org/appliances/appliance-recalls/midea-air-conditioners-recalled-due-to-mold-risk-a6544941996/ Midea Just Recalled This Popular Air Conditioner - NBC News https://www.nbcnews.com/select/shopping/midea-air-conditioner-recall-rcna211324 31 sources Mixture-of-Agents gpt-5 Claude Sonnet 4 Gemini 2.5 Flash Reflection ### Strengths and Weaknesses of Individual Models #### Gemini-2.5-Flash - **Strengths:** This model provides a comprehensive list of affected brands and models. It clearly explains where to find the model number on your unit and provides detailed instructions on what to do if your unit is recalled, including refund and repair options. - **Weaknesses:** Although thorough, it can be overwhelming due to its length and the number of external references cluttering the text, making it less readable. It also lacks a concise step-by-step guide for users. #### Claude-Sonnet-4 - **Strengths:** This model organizes information into well-defined sections and steps, making it easy to follow. It clearly outlines each step to determine if a unit is recalled and options available for affected users. - **Weaknesses:** The response might be perceived as lengthy due to the excessive details on individual steps, potentially causing users to lose focus. It slightly repeats details in both the explanation and steps sections. #### GPT-5 - **Strengths:** Presents a clear, step-by-step method to determine a unit's recall status, including what to do if it is affected. It effectively streamlines the content, making it user-friendly and easily digestible. - **Weaknesses:** The model might seem less comprehensive than others, as it lacks the detailed background on the recall or a full list of affected brands and models, which could be vital for users seeking more context. ### Key Insights - All models highlight the need to check the model and serial number on the air conditioning unit. - They consistently mention the recall affecting Midea U and U+ models sold under various brand names from March 2020 to May 2025. - They all agree on two actions if a unit is recalled: seeking repair or a refund. ### Cross-Check with Search Results - The models' answers are consistent with the search results, which confirm the recall details, model numbers, and steps for consumers who own recalled units. - The comprehensive lists and detailed steps provided align well with the official recall information. ### Overall Evaluation All responses are detailed and accurate but differ in structure and comprehensiveness. Gemini-2.5-flash offers a detailed list of models, Claude-Sonnet-4 provides well-organized steps, and GPT-5 gives a concise and coherent guide for checking recall status and taking action. Each has its strengths, and their insights are mostly synchronous with the available information. How to Determine if Your Midea Air Conditioner is Recalled Due to Mold Exposure To find out if your Midea air conditioning unit is part of the recall for mold exposure detailed by the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC), follow these steps: Step 1: Locate the Model and Serial Number Model Number Location: Check the front right side of your air conditioning unit when facing it. The label will display the model number you need. Serial Number: This is also on the unit and will help verify if your unit is included in the recall. Step 2: Identify Recalled Models and Brands The recall affects Midea U and U+ window air conditioners sold from March 2020 through May 2025. These units were sold under several brand names such as Midea, Comfort Aire, Danby, Frigidaire, Insignia, Keystone, LBG Products, Mr. Cool, Perfect Aire, and Sea Breeze123. Step 3: Verify Your Unit's Status Official Website: Go to the Midea recall website at www.MideaUrecall.expertinquiry.com and input your model and serial number to check if your unit is affected12. Affected Units Details These units are typically white, measure about 22 inches wide and 14 inches high, and come in 8,000, 10,000, and 12,000 BTU sizes. They include remote controls and can be controlled via a mobile app179. What to Do If Your Unit is Recalled Stop Using the Unit: Discontinue use of the affected unit to prevent possible health risks from mold exposure. Refund Options: Midea offers a full refund for units purchased within the last 36 months. Units older may be subject to prorated refunds ranging from 80% to 50%, depending on their age5. You can apply for a refund by returning the unit or providing a photograph showing you have cut the unplugged power cord12. Repair Options: Midea can send a technician for a new drain plug installation or provide a repair kit with a new drain plug and bubble level for self-repair, depending on your model12. Use While Awaiting Repair: If you choose to keep using the unit while waiting for repair, carefully follow Midea’s inspection steps to check for visible signs of mold and ensure proper drainage115. Contact Midea Phone: For further assistance and confirmation, or to initiate your refund or repair, contact Midea at 888-345-0256. Email/Online Support: You can also email at midea4028@midea.com or visit the official recall website for more details and directions on next steps36. Mind Map Expand Model Number Location Serial Number Step 1: Locate Model & Serial Number Affected Models Brands Included Step 2: Identify Recalled Models Official Website Step 3: Verify Unit's Status Unit Specifications Affected Units Details Stop Using Unit Refund Options Repair Options Use While Awaiting Repair What to Do If Recalled Phone Support Email Support Contact Midea Determine Midea AC Recall Status How to safely inspect my air conditioner for mold? What are the health risks associated with mold exposure? How to dispose of a recalled air conditioner safely? Costco has a midea 12,000 btu unit on sale . Is the current costco model on sale one of the recalled units? Midea 12000 BTU DUO Portable Air Conditioner with MShield https://www.costco.com/midea-12%2C000-btu-duo-portable-air-conditioner-with-mshield.product.4000237574.html Midea U-Shaped 12k BTU Window Air Conditioner | Costco https://www.costco.com/midea-u-shaped-12k-btu-window-air-conditioner.product.4000104274.html Midea U 12,000 BTU Smart Inverter Window AC with MShield ... https://www.costco.com/midea-u-12%2C000-btu-smart-inverter-window-ac-with-mshield%2C-energy-star.product.4000380426.html 25 sources Mixture-of-Agents gpt-5 Claude Sonnet 4 Gemini 2.5 Flash Reflection ### Reflection on Answers and Reference Information 1. **gemini-2.5-flash**: - **Strengths**: Provides detailed information about the recall of the Midea U and U+ window air conditioners, including symptoms experienced by consumers and the recall process steps such as repair options and refund mechanisms. - **Weaknesses**: Lacks clarity in distinguishing between recalled models and currently available models at Costco. 2. **claude-sonnet-4**: - **Strengths**: Distinctly separates recalled models from those not affected by the recall, specifically mentioning the Midea 12,000 BTU DUO Portable Air Conditioner as not recalled. Offers a detailed explanation of the recall process. - **Weaknesses**: Slight repetition in parts of the explanation about the recall process. 3. **gpt-5**: - **Strengths**: Clearly differentiates between recalled U/U+ window models and the non-recalled DUO Portable model. Offers practical steps consumers can take to identify if their unit is part of the recall. - **Weaknesses**: Somewhat verbose in explanation; could be more concise in describing which model is affected by the recall. 4. **Reference Information**: - Primarily supports the recall of Midea U and U+ window units due to mold risk from pooled water and provides information on models affected, the recall process, and consumer safety commission announcements. - Confirms that the Midea DUO Portable Air Conditioner is not part of the recall, which matches the non-recalled units as described in the responses. Current Midea 12,000 BTU Unit Status at Costco Recalled Units The Midea U and U+ 12,000 BTU Smart Inverter Window AC models are subject to a recall due to a design flaw that causes water pooling inside the unit, leading to mold growth. This recall covers units sold between March 2020 and May 2025, with approximately 1.7 million units affected11131415. Affected models from this recall include MAW12U1QWT, MAW12V1QWT, MAW12AV1QWT, among other MAW12… variants. Consumers experiencing issues with these units should contact Midea for repair or a prorated refund1113. Non-Recalled Models Currently, Costco is promoting the Midea 12,000 BTU DUO Portable Air Conditioner with MShield on sale. This unit is a portable model and is not part of the U/U+ window AC recall167. It features inverter technology and offers significant energy savings, designed with a dual-hose system that prevents drainage issues17. Consumer Advice For customers considering a purchase from Costco: Check the Model Number: If considering a Midea window unit, verify its model number against the recall list. Portable Models: The DUO Portable unit is not affected by the recall and is safe to buy and use. Recall Process for Recalled Units: Consumers with recalled units should utilize Midea’s dedicated recall website or hotline for repair or refund services, as listed in recall announcements1113. While the recall prompted major retailers to intercept sales of affected units in mid-May 2025, some Costco locations have continued limited sales of these units into July 2025, as observed in South Carolina and New Jersey5. As of now, the DUO Portable Air Conditioner is the popular choice available at Costco, bypassing any recall issues167. Mind Map Expand Models under recall Affected units Major models Consumer actions Recalled Units Current promotion at Costco Features Non-Recalled Models Purchasing guidance Recall process Consumer Advice Intercept sales of recalled units Current popular choice Retailer Actions Midea 12,000 BTU Unit Status at Costco Current availability of Midea air conditioners at Costco Details on the Midea air conditioner recall process Differences between Midea DUO Portable and U-shaped models Mixture-of-Agents Search Web"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=2e463462-e9a7-4b62-8586-4abd0eb43a7d","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=2e463462-e9a7-4b62-8586-4abd0eb43a7d"}]}]}]
